      "body" : "> I agree, but surely we should be factoring in the protocol version nevertheless?\r\n\r\nNo. There is still no obligation for any participant in the p2p network to support an optional message type just because they sent you a specific protocol version. If this was documented in some kind of BIP and both peers in the connection supported that BIP, then sure. Though, this case in this thread isn't documented anywhere and wouldn't make sense anyway.",
